docs.abstract: The former Minneapolis police officer is awaiting trial on murder and manslaughter charges after a video captured him kneeling on Mr. Floyd’s neck in May.
docs.snippet: The former Minneapolis police officer is awaiting trial on murder and manslaughter charges after a video captured him kneeling on Mr. Floyd’s neck in May.
docs.lead_paragraph: For months, protesters trained their anger on Derek Chauvin, a former Minneapolis police officer who was shown on video holding his knee on the neck of George Floyd before his death. They demonstrated outside of Mr. Chauvin’s home, posted his mug shot across the internet and chanted outside his first in-person court appearance last month.

headline.main: Derek Chauvin, Ex-Officer Charged in George Floyd’s Death, Is Released on Bail
headline.print_headline: Former Minneapolis Officer Charged in Floyd’s Death Is Released on $100,000 Bail

docs.abstract: Supervisors denied civil-rights prosecutors’ request to use a grand jury for their investigation into the 2014 shooting of a Black boy by a Cleveland police officer, but did not tell his family.
docs.snippet: Supervisors denied civil-rights prosecutors’ request to use a grand jury for their investigation into the 2014 shooting of a Black boy by a Cleveland police officer, but did not tell his family.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Justice Department decided more than a year ago to effectively shut down its civil-rights investigation into the high-profile killing of Tamir Rice, a 12-year-old Black boy carrying a pellet gun who was shot by a Cleveland police officer in 2014, according to people familiar with the matter.

headline.main: Justice Dept. Is Said to Quietly Quash Inquiry Into Tamir Rice Killing
headline.print_headline: Justice Dept. Is Said To Quietly Quash Inquiry Into Black Child’s Killing

byline.original: By Charlie Savage and Katie Benner

docs.abstract: A judge gave grand jurors in the case permission to speak publicly, a rare move that immediately led one juror to speak out.
docs.snippet: A judge gave grand jurors in the case permission to speak publicly, a rare move that immediately led one juror to speak out.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOUISVILLE, Ky. — A Kentucky judge on Tuesday granted grand jurors in the Breonna Taylor case permission to speak publicly, a rare move that immediately led one juror to assert that prosecutors had not given the panel the opportunity to bring homicide charges in the case.

headline.main: Breonna Taylor Grand Juror Says Homicide Charges Were Not Presented
headline.print_headline: Grand Juror in Taylor Case Says Prosecutors Never Presented Homicide Charges

docs.abstract: An exchange between Vice President Mike Pence and Senator Kamala Harris late in the debate crystallized the deep differences in the two sides’ approaches to racial justice.
docs.lead_paragraph: An exchange between Vice President Mike Pence and Senator Kamala Harris late in the debate crystallized the deep differences in the two sides’ approaches to racial justice.

headline.main: An exchange about Breonna Taylor and George Floyd crystallizes the candidates’ opposing views on racial justice.

docs.abstract: The toll was unclear, but witnesses said several people were shot during  demonstrations against police brutality in Lagos. The governor said “miscreants” had hijacked mostly peaceful protests.
docs.snippet: The toll was unclear, but witnesses said several people were shot during  demonstrations against police brutality in Lagos. The governor said “miscreants” had hijacked mostly peaceful protests.
docs.lead_paragraph: LAGOS, Nigeria — Nigerian security forces opened fire Tuesday night at a demonstration in Lagos against police brutality, hitting several people according to witnesses, in a major escalation of the unrest that has gripped the country for two weeks.

headline.print_headline: Nigerian Forces Shoot at Demonstrators Against Police Brutality

docs.abstract: The judge upheld the more serious charge of second-degree murder against Derek Chauvin, the former Minneapolis police officer who was captured on video kneeling on Mr. Floyd’s neck.
docs.snippet: The judge upheld the more serious charge of second-degree murder against Derek Chauvin, the former Minneapolis police officer who was captured on video kneeling on Mr. Floyd’s neck.
docs.lead_paragraph: A judge has dropped a third-degree murder charge against Derek Chauvin, the former Minneapolis police officer accused of killing George Floyd on May 25 by kneeling on his neck for more than eight minutes.

headline.main: Judge Dismisses Third-Degree Murder Charge in George Floyd Killing

docs.abstract: Diversity and inclusion programs for elites are tokens. A large wage increase that would most benefit the Black working class is far better.
docs.snippet: Diversity and inclusion programs for elites are tokens. A large wage increase that would most benefit the Black working class is far better.
docs.lead_paragraph: After a summer of protests over the killing of George Floyd broadened into a wider reckoning on racial injustice, corporate America and the political establishment unleashed a flurry of promises to combat systemic racism. Diversity initiatives have been launched; high-profile companies in several sectors have settled on the advancement of a few people of color in their hierarchies.

headline.main: To Reduce Racial Inequality, Raise the Minimum Wage

byline.original: By Ellora Derenoncourt and Claire Montialoux

docs.abstract: President Trump came to the debate ready with his regular wrap on race when asked to explain his description of “Black Lives Matter” as a symbol of hate: He claimed he had done more than any president since Abraham Lincoln for African-Americans, and he called himself the “least racist person in this room.” (Never mind that the moderator of the debate, Kristen Welker, is a Black woman.)
docs.lead_paragraph: President Trump came to the debate ready with his regular wrap on race when asked to explain his description of “Black Lives Matter” as a symbol of hate: He claimed he had done more than any president since Abraham Lincoln for African-Americans, and he called himself the “least racist person in this room.” (Never mind that the moderator of the debate, Kristen Welker, is a Black woman.)

headline.main: Biden calls Trump ‘one of the most racist presidents we’ve had in modern history.’

docs.abstract: The rapper and activist on transforming fear into power.
docs.snippet: The rapper and activist on transforming fear into power.
docs.lead_paragraph: You might know Michael Render, a.k.a. Killer Mike, from a speech he made that went viral four days after George Floyd’s death. Protests in Atlanta were escalating and so was the damage and violence. The mayor needed help turning the temperature down.

headline.main: Killer Mike Says He Has a Choice to Make

docs.abstract: Police officers and sheriff’s deputies in Graham, N.C., deployed a chemical spray and arrested eight people at a get-out-the-vote march and rally on Saturday, according to the police and participants.
docs.snippet: Police officers and sheriff’s deputies in Graham, N.C., deployed a chemical spray and arrested eight people at a get-out-the-vote march and rally on Saturday, according to the police and participants.
docs.lead_paragraph: Police officers and sheriff’s deputies in Graham, N.C., deployed a chemical spray and arrested eight people at a march and rally on Saturday that were intended to honor George Floyd and encourage people to vote, according to the police and participants.

headline.main: Police in North Carolina use a chemical spray to disperse a get-out-the-vote rally.
